value.value: QC metric related to an extracted ion chromatogram.
QC metric related to the mass spectrometry acquisition.
QC metric related to events in the ion source.
QC metric based on MS1 events.
QC metric based on MS2 events.
QC metric related to the sample preparation.
QC metric related to measurements of the ambient environment, such as the laboratory.
Representation of the ion current assigned to detected precursors in the series of all MS1 spectra versus time.
The median of the distribution of observed fragment mass accuracies (MS:4000072) [in ppm] of identified MS2 spectra after user-defined acceptance criteria (FDR) are applied.

definition.value: Factors like temperature, airflow, or instrument calibration can cause mass shifts.

value.value: The mean of the distribution of observed fragment mass accuracies (MS:4000072) [in ppm] of identified MS2 spectra after user-defined acceptance criteria (FDR) are applied

definition.value: Factors like temperature, airflow, or instrument calibration can cause mass shifts. See MS:4000178 for the MS1 equivalent.

value.value: The standard deviation of the distribution of observed fragment mass accuracies (MS:4000072) [in ppm] of identified MS2 spectra after user-defined acceptance criteria (FDR) are applied

definition.value: Factors like temperature, airflow, or instrument calibration can cause mass shifts.  See MS:4000179 for the MS1 equivalent.

value.value: The area under the total ion current chromatogram (MS:1000235) of all MS1 spectra.

definition.value: The metric informs about the dynamic range of the acquisition. Differences between samples of an experiment may indicate differences in the dynamic range and/or in the sample content. The signal can be affected by contamination, retention time shifts, or loss of hydrophilic/hydrophobic peptides.

value.value: The area under the total ion current chromatogram (MS:1000235) of all MS2 spectra.

definition.value: The metric informs about the dynamic range of the acquisition. Differences between samples of an experiment may indicate differences in the dynamic range and/or in the sample content. The signal can be affected by contamination, retention time shifts, or loss of hydrophilic/hydrophobic peptides. Issues such as contamination on the MS front-end and fragmentation efficiency can lead to poor MS signals. Contamination would decrease both MS1 and MS2 S/N, while poor fragmentation efficiency affects MS2 signal but leaves MS1 signal unchanged.

label.value: peak area of MS1 vs MS2 signal ratio

value.value: The ratio of the area under TIC of MS1 (MS:4000029) divided by the area under the TIC of MS2 (MS:4000030).

definition.value: Poor fragmentation efficiency or precursor fragmentation intensity thresholds affect MS2 signal but leave MS1 signal unchanged.

value.value: The number of XIC that account for the top half of all XIC-FWHM divided by the number of all XIC.

definition.value: This metric characterises the distribution of precursor peak widths, much as the N50 characterises contig sizes in genome assembly.

value.value: The first to n-th quantile of peak widths for XICs. A metric's value triplet represents the related QuaMeter metrics of XIC-FWHM-Q1,Q2,Q3.

The log ratio of successive XIC height quartiles. The metric's value triplet represents the log ratios of XIC-height-Q2 to XIC-height-Q1, XIC-height-Q3 to XIC-height-Q2, XIC-height max to XIC-height-Q3.
The retention time duration of the chromatography in seconds.

definition.value: Longer duration may indicate a better chromatographic separation of compounds which depends, however, also on the sampling/scan rate of the MS instrument.

value.value: The interval when the respective quarter of the TIC accumulates divided by retention time duration.

definition.value: The metric informs about the dynamic range of the acquisition along the chromatographic separation. The metric provides information on the sample (compound) flow along the chromatographic run, potentially revealing poor chromatographic performance, such as the absence of a signal for a significant portion of the run.

value.value: The interval used for acquisition of the first, second, third, and fourth quarter of all MS1 events divided by retention time duration.

definition.value: The metric informs about the dynamic range of the acquisition along the chromatographic separation. For MS1 scans, the values are expected to be in a similar range across samples of the same type.

value.value: The interval used for acquisition of the first, second, third, and fourth quarter of all MS2 events divided by retention time duration.

definition.value: The metric informs about the dynamic range of the acquisition along the chromatographic separation. For MS2 scans, the comparability of the values depends on the acquisition mode and settings to select ions for fragmentation.

value.value: The log ratios of successive TIC-change quartiles. The TIC changes are the list of MS1 total ion current (TIC) value changes from one to the next scan, produced when each MS1 TIC is subtracted from the preceding MS1 TIC. The metric's value triplet represents the log ratio of the TIC-change Q2 to Q1, Q3 to Q2, TIC-change-max to Q3

definition.value: The metric informs about the dynamic range of the acquisition along the chromatographic separation.This metric evaluates the stability (similarity) of MS1 TIC values from scan to scan along the LC run. High log ratios representing very large intensity differences between pairs of scans might be due to electrospray instability or presence of a chemical contaminant.

value.value: The log ratios of successive TIC quartiles. The metric's value triplet represents the log ratios of TIC-Q2 to TIC-Q1, TIC-Q3 to TIC-Q2, TIC-max to TIC-Q3.

definition.value: The metric informs about the dynamic range of the acquisition along the chromatographic separation. The ratios provide information on the distribution of the TIC values for one LC-MS run. Within an experiment, with the same LC setup, values should be comparable between samples.

value.value: The number of MS1 events in the run.

definition.value: An unusual low number may indicate incomplete sampling/scan rate of the MS instrument, low sample volume and/or failed injection of a sample.

value.value: The number of MS2 events in the run.

definition.value: An unusual low number may indicate incomplete sampling/scan rate of the MS instrument, low sample volume and/or failed injection of a sample.

value.value: The first to n-th quantile of MS1 peak density (scan peak counts). A value triplet represents the original QuaMeter metrics, the quartiles of MS1 density. The number of values in the tuple implies the quantile mode.

The first to n-th quantile of MS2 peak density (scan peak counts). A value triplet represents the original QuaMeter metrics, the quartiles of MS2 density. The number of values in the tuple implies the quantile mode.

The fraction of MS/MS precursors of the corresponding charge. The fractions [0,1] are given in the 'Fraction' column, corresponding charges in the 'Charge state' column. The highest charge state is to be interpreted as that charge state or higher.

definition.value: the MS2-PrecZ metrics can be directly read from the table respective table rows, the ratios of IS-3 metrics must be derived from the respective table rows, IS-3A as ratio of +1 over +2, IS-3B as ratio of +3 over +2, IS-3C as +4 over +2.

label.value: MS2 unknown and likely precursor charges fractions

value.value: The fractions of inferred charge state of MS/MS precursors. The fractions [0,1] are given in the 'Fraction' column, corresponding charges in the 'Charge state' column. Charge 0 represents unknown charge states.

label.value: fastest frequency for MS level 1 collection

value.value: Fastest frequency for MS level 1 collection

definition.value: Spectrum acquisition frequency can be used to gauge the suitability of used instrument settings for the sample content used.

label.value: fastest frequency for MS level 2 collection

value.value: Fastest frequency for MS level 2 collection

definition.value: Spectrum acquisition frequency can be used to gauge the suitability of used instrument settings for the sample content used.

value.value: The duration of the mass spectrometry acquisition (as measured by the time between the last scan and first scan) in seconds.

The minimal proportion of peaks needed to account for at least 50% of the total ion current in each individual spectrum considered, recorded in a mandatory fraction column. Either USI or native spectrum identifier columns must be present as well.
Upper and lower limit of m/z precursor values at which MSn spectra are recorded.

definition.value: The metric informs about the dynamic range of the acquisition. Based on the used MS instrument configuration, the values should be similar. Variations between measurements may arise when employing acquisition in DDA mode.

value.value: Upper and lower limit of retention time at which spectra are recorded.

definition.value: An unusual low range may indicate incomplete sampling and/or a premature or failed LC run.

value.value: The number of chromatograms recorded for the run.
Observed mass accuracy in ppm, calculated by 1E6 x (observed m/z - theoretical m/z)/theoretical m/z of a selected and identified ion in a mass spectrum.
A QC metric based on a QC sample of known content.
A QC metric based on a QC sample of known and high complexity content.
A QC metric based on a QC sample of known and low complexity content.
A QC metric based on the results of a QC2 sample measurement. A QC2 sample is made from Pierce HeLa protein digest standard, see Pichler et al. Chiva et al. for details on QC sample design.

definition.value: Expected peptides from QC2 sample measurement are: 'YAEAVTR','STLTDSLVC(Carbamidomethyl)K','SLADELALVDVLEDK','NPDDITNEEYGEFYK','LAVDEEENADNNTK','FEELNMDLFR','EAALSTALSEK','DDVAQTDLLQIDPNFGSK','RFPGYDSESK','EATTEFSVDAR','EQFLDGDGWTSR','TPAQFDADELR','LGDLYEEEMR','EVSTYIK','FAFQAEVNR'

value.value: A QC metric based on the results of a QC1 sample measurement. A QC1 sample is made from trypsin-digested BSA MS Standard (CAM modified), see Pichler et al. Chiva et al. for details on QC sample design).

definition.value: Expected peptides from QC1 sample measurement are: 'LVNELTEFAK','HLVDEPQNLIK','VPQVSTPTLVEVSR','EAC(Carbamidomethyl)FAVEGPK','EYEATLEEC(Carbamidomethyl)C(Carbamidomethyl)AK','EC(Carbamidomethyl)C(Carbamidomethyl)HGDLLEC(Carbamidomethyl)ADDR','SLHTLFGDELC(Carbamidomethyl)K','TC(Carbamidomethyl)VADESHAGC(Carbamidomethyl)EK','YIC(Carbamidomethyl)DNQDTISSK','NEC(Carbamidomethyl)FLSHK'

value.value: Observed mass accuracy for the peptides of a QC2 sample measurement. The table should contain the peptides as described in the QC2 sample metric term, missing are interpreted as not detected.

Observed intensities for the peptides of a QC2 sample measurement within 5 ppm and +/- 240 s RT tolerance. Different metrics of observed intensities are possible, at least one must be present. The table should contain the peptides as defined in the parent QC2 sample metric term, missing are interpreted as not detected.
